---
// "Built for Real Workflows" section — 3 panels + CTA.
---

<section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 md:py-20" data-reveal id="use-cases">
  <p class="text-center font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-green)] mb-3">
    Workflows
  </p>
  <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-center tracking-tight">
    Built for Real Workflows
  </h2>
  <p class="text-center text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12 leading-relaxed">
    From production deployment to multi-channel team collaboration — OMA is
    designed for how engineering teams actually operate.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
    <article data-lift class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] p-6 hover:border-[var(--color-border-strong)]">
      <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-brand-subtle)] flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shrink-0">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-brand)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <polyline points="4 17 10 11 4 5" />
          <line x1="12" y1="19" x2="20" y2="19" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2 tracking-tight">Deploy &amp; Operate</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        Kubernetes-native with health checks, HPA scaling, and Prometheus metrics.
        Run on Cloudflare or your own cluster &mdash; same code, same API.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article data-lift class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] p-6 hover:border-[var(--color-border-strong)]">
      <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-blue-subtle)] flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shrink-0">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-blue)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2 tracking-tight">Multi-Channel</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        Slack, Telegram, Linear &mdash; agents as real teammates with their own
        identity, @mentionable, assignable, and threaded.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article data-lift class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] p-6 hover:border-[var(--color-border-strong)]">
      <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-green-subtle)] flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shrink-0">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-green)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2 tracking-tight">Managed State</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        Crashes? Sessions resume from the last event. Append-only SQLite log
        means no data loss, no partial turns.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 text-center">
    <a
      href="https://docs.oma.duyet.net/quickstart"
      class="inline-flex px-6 py-3 rounded-md bg-[var(--color-fg)] text-[var(--color-bg)] font-medium font-display no-underline hover:no-underline"
    >
      Get Started &rarr;
    </a>
  </div>
</section>
